			<name>
				<baseName xml:lang="en">Direct combustion｜Electricity｜biomass boiler（30MW）</baseName>
				<baseName xml:lang="zh">直接燃烧发电｜电力｜生物质锅炉（30MW）</baseName>
			</name>
			<classificationInformation>
				<common:classification>
					<common:class level="0">Energy carriers and technologies</common:class>
					<common:class level="1">Heat and steam</common:class>
				</common:classification>
			</classificationInformation>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">The biomass boiler with a capacity of 30 MW represents a unit process that generates electricity via direct combustion. It is designed to convert biomass, specifically 1 ton of wheat straw, into thermal energy which is then used for electric power generation. Such a process can be integrated into renewable energy systems and supports electricity supply in regions with available biomass resources.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">30MW 生物质锅炉代表一个通过直接燃烧产生电力的单元过程。它旨在将生物质，特别是1吨小麦秸秆，转换为热能，进而用于发电。该过程可以集成到可再生能源系统中，并支持具有可用生物质资源的地区的电力供应。</common:generalComment>
		</dataSetInformation>
		<quantitativeReference type="Reference flow(s)">
			<functionalUnitOrOther xml:lang="en">taking 1 ton of wheat straw as the functional unit</functionalUnitOrOther>
			<referenceToReferenceFlow>4</referenceToReferenceFlow>
		</quantitativeReference>
